<head>CUT HAIR</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">剃頭</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">薙</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>CUT HAIR.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Tì 薙／鬄／剃／剔 originally referred to the shaving off of children's hair, but the word came to refer quite generally to all manner of shaving or cutting of hair.</p>
<p>2. Kūn 髡 refers specifically to the shaving off of adult's hair.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>理髮 is the standard modern term for cutting hair.</p>
<p>剃頭 is the standard modern term for shaving the head.</p>
<p>推頭 (coll) refers to taking a hair-cut (as opposed to giving someone a hair-cut)</p>
<p>開光 (informal) refers teasingly to taking a haircut.</p>
<p>整容 (lit) is a dignified way of referring to taking a hair-cut.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
    </div>
